From: H618 video enablement <noreply@local>
Subject: [PATCH] media: cedrus: drop tiled NV12_32L32 output so linear NV12 is used

The DE33 (H616/H618) display-engine VI plane can only scan out LINEAR
framebuffers. v4l2request prefers the tiled NV12_32L32 capture format, which
then fails to commit on the linear-only overlay plane. Cedrus supports linear
output (UNTILED), so remove the tiled format to force linear NV12 and enable
zero-copy direct-to-plane video. Rebased onto the current cedrus format list.
---
--- a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_video.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_video.c
@@ -77,10 +77,6 @@
 		.capabilities	= CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_UNTILED,
 	},
 	{
-		.pixelformat	= V4L2_PIX_FMT_NV12_32L32,
-		.directions	= CEDRUS_DECODE_DST,
-	},
-	{
 		.pixelformat	= V4L2_PIX_FMT_NV21,
 		.directions	= CEDRUS_DECODE_DST,
 		.capabilities	= CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_UNTILED,
